parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Overheating and Cooling System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure. It can also cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the vehicle overheats
the coolant level is low
the thermostat housing fails
the water outlet fails
the radiator fluid is low
the AC doesn't cool.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Turbocharger failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to accelerate or climb hills. This can increase the risk of accidents, especially when merging into traffic or ascending steep grades.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates when started
the vehicle is slow to respond when accelerating
the vehicle is slow to gain forward momentum.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Camshaft and VVT system failure can cause the engine to run poorly, leading to decreased performance and fuel efficiency. It can also cause the check engine light to come on, which can lead to costly repairs if left unchecked.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
error code P0011 (camshaft
VVT bank 1 too advanced) is displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents. It can also cause fires, which can result in damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
flames form from underneath the radio
the vehicle catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and cutting off can cause the vehicle to lose power, increasing the risk of accidents. It can also cause inconvenience and frustration for the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or cuts off
the engine light comes on
error code P2076 is displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Valve cover failure can cause oil leaks, which can lead to engine damage and costly repairs.
symptoms: The valve cover fails
oil leaks are present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the driver and passengers may not receive the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
even when the vehicle sustains significant damage
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Carbon monoxide poisoning can cause serious health problems, including headaches, dizziness, nausea, and even death, especially if the driver is unaware of the issue.
symptoms: Driver experiences blacking out
memory problems
and severe back pain while driving
with high levels of carbon monoxide detected in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended vehicle movement can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is in motion or in a confined space.
symptoms: Vehicle crashes into a pole or another vehicle without warning
resulting in damage and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock up, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks up
the vehicle loses power steering
the dashboard displays "Service Power Steering" or "Service Stabilitrak" warnings
the vehicle shuts off while driving
the steering wheel tightens up and becomes difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A low-capacity or faulty battery can prevent the power steering system from functioning properly, leading to steering issues and safety risks.
symptoms: The battery voltage is low
the power steering system fails to operate
the dashboard displays "Service Power Steering" or "Service Stabilitrak" warnings
the vehicle shuts off while driving.
